If there is no such character, return '_'.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef first_non_repeating(s: str) -> str:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string consisting of lowercase English letters.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the first non-repeating character in the string. If there is no such character, return '_'.\\n\", \"code\": \"from collections import Counter\\n\\ndef first_non_repeating(s: str) -> str:\\n    char_counts = Counter(s)\\n    for char in s:\\n        if char_counts[char] == 1:\\n            return char\\n    return '_'\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert first_non_repeating('abcabc') == '_' \", \"assert first_non_repeating('aabbccddee') == '_'\", \"assert first_non_repeating('hello') == 'h'\", \"assert first_non_repeating('world') == 'w'\"] }"
